-- Car Blast Leaves Russian Mufti Wounded, Deputy Is Shot Dead
-- B y   P a u l   A b e l s k y
-- 2012-07-19T08:56:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/car-blast-leaves-russian-mufti-wounded-deputy-is-shot-dead-1-.html
The top cleric in Tatarstan, a
Muslim-majority republic in central  Russia , was injured in a car
blast today and his deputy was shot dead when leaving his house
at about the same time, the  Interior Ministry  said.  Ildus Khazrat Faizov was at the wheel of his car in the
regional capital of Kazan at the time of the explosion at 10:15
a.m., the ministry’s branch in Tatarstan  said  on its website.
Valiulla Yakupov was killed at about 10 a.m. when an unknown
assailant fired several shots, Russia’s Investigative Committee
said in a separate  statement .  Security was tightened around all important religious sites
and officials in the republic, according to the Interior
Ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
